<div id="banner">
	<h1>How is Disney like the Soviet Union?</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>James B. Stewart, <em>New Yorker</em> writer and author of <a href="http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0684809931/ref=nosim/coolbooks02/">DisneyWar</a> explains in an interview given at the Stanford Bookstore as part of his DisneyWar book tour.</p>

<p><a href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/static/disneywar.mp3">Listen to low-quality 18 minute 10.4MB MP3.</a></p>

<p>Five year plans, sham democracies, purging of unloyal party members&#8230; it&#8217;s all there.</p>

<p>(Sadly, my battery ran out afterwards so I didn&#8217;t get to record his fun stories about riding in SUVs with Michael Eisner.)</p>

<p class="posted">posted March 16, 2005 01:50 AM (<a class="category" href="cat_education">Education</a>) (<a href="#comments">0 comments</a>) <a href="001618" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

